ptouch-print by Dominic Radermacher and the ptouch-print contributors, which
is licensed under the GNU General Public License version 3.

    ptouch-print: https://git.familie-radermacher.ch/linux/ptouch-print.git

The Brother P-Touch device table, capability flags, status protocol, command
construction, and raster bit-packing in ptouch-rs are based on that work, so
those parts and the distributed binaries are licensed GPL-3.0-or-later. With
gratitude to the ptouch-print authors for the reverse engineering that made
this possible.

The protocol implementation is additionally informed by Brother's published
command references and by the device behavior documented in these projects:

    Brother PT-P900/P900W/P950NW Raster Command Reference
    https://download.brother.com/welcome/docp100407/cv_ptp900_eng_raster_102.pdf

    Brother PT-9700PC/PT-9800PCN ESC/P Command Reference
    https://download.brother.com/welcome/docp000584/cv_pt9700_eng_escp_103.pdf

    printer-driver-ptouch: https://github.com/philpem/printer-driver-ptouch
    rasterprynt: https://github.com/boxine/rasterprynt
    pyPTouch: https://github.com/amathieson/pyPTouch

With thanks to their authors for documenting these printers.

Original, independently written parts of this project (the egui GUI, the
command-line front end, and the rendering code other than raster conversion)
